  "original_title": "21 \u0b9a\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0bae\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbf \u0b93\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8:   \u0baa\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 13 \u0b86\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bc8",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "21 boys threatened with homosexuality: Journalist jailed for 13 years",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "A POCSO fast-track court has sentenced a journalist to 13 years in prison after convicting him in two cases of intimidation and homosexuality.",
        "He used to take school children to forest areas with words of desire and indulged in homosexuality. And he has repeatedly engaged in homosexuality with those boys by threatening to record it as a video on his cell phone.",
        "This incident took place on 28th of 2018. The journalist was found to have forced 21 boys into homosexuality. In this regard, 16 cases were registered in Bindur police, 3 cases in Gangolli police, one case each in Guntabura suburb and Kollur police.",
        "Cases related to this are going on in Udupi District Additional Court and POCSO Fast Track Court. So far judgment has been given in 11 cases. In 8 of these cases he was acquitted saying that the charges against him were not proved.",
        "At this stage, in 2 cases against him, the court has given sensational verdict. That is, in one case he has been sentenced to 10 years imprisonment and a fine of Rs.1,000 and in another case to 3 years rigorous imprisonment and a fine of Rs.1,000."
      ],
